---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | TGO Network" description="Brand and organization overview for the TGO Network prototype.">
  <main class="page-shell page-stack">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Static Page</span>
        <h1>About</h1>
        <p>
          TGO Network is being shaped as a content-led platform with city pages, editorial programming, events, and a
          staff admin workflow. The first implementation goal is not feature breadth, but a system that can evolve
          cleanly without replacing its foundations later.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section detail-grid">
      <article class="panel prose-panel">
        <div class="card-label">What is being built</div>
        <p>
          The platform separates the public site, admin console, and API so content delivery, operations, and business
          rules can scale independently.
        </p>
        <p>
          Astro handles the public presentation layer, Vue powers the staff workflows, and Hono owns the application
          boundary for data, auth, and permissions.
        </p>
      </article>

      <aside class="panel panel-soft">
        <div class="card-label">Current focus</div>
        <ul class="meta-list">
          <li>Shared contracts between frontend and backend</li>
          <li>Static-first public routes with real API shapes</li>
          <li>Admin and auth groundwork for later operations</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
